        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 19 at 3:19PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 317 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fort Carson, or near Colorado Springs, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Very heavy rainfall and Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea
size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible. Earlier this afternoon, a thunderstorm in the
Monument area produced 3.43 inches if rain in a little more
than 1 hour.

Locations impacted include...
Southeastern Colorado Springs, Fountain, Hanover, Stratmoor, Fort
Carson, Security, Security-Widefield, and Peterson Space Force Base.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
